Skiing with our 2 year old 🙌 Part 2 🤍🥹 I'm not an expert, but I feel like at this age (2 almost 3), time on skis and just getting used to how they feel is more important than a ton of instruction. That doesn't mean I don't try, haha, but little kids just need time to experiment and try things in a safe environment. They learn everything from trying it out. Also, a lot of skiing is not actually skiing. Sitting on the chair lift, standing on the "magic carpets", sitting or resting. I know it's not always possible, but trying to make the in-between moments fun as well will add to the overall positive experience that will make them want to come back for more. Feel free to share your tips about skiing with toddlers! Scientists in Japan, led by molecular biologist Masatsugu Toyota, made a groundbreaking discovery in plant communication, published in Nature Communications. Their research unveils real-time footage of plants responding to stress signals through volatile organic compounds (VOCs) emitted by neighboring stressed plants. The study sheds light on a defense mechanism against environmental threats, utilizing genetically engineered Arabidopsis plants and a fluorescence microscope for monitoring stress signals. This breakthrough builds on 1983 observations, revealing the intricate language of plants through chemical, electrical, and underground signaling. 🎥 Masatsugu Toyota/ Saitama University

Bubu and Dudu always slept together in a cozy bed with a single blanket. But sometimes, they would fight over who gets more of the blanket. One night, Bubu decided to play a game with Dudu. She said, "Let's see who can hold the most of the blanket. The winner gets to sleep comfortably, and the loser has to tell a joke." Dudu agreed, thinking he could easily win. They both pulled the blanket from each other, trying to cover themselves. But Bubu was smarter and faster than Dudu. She quickly wrapped herself in the blanket, leaving Dudu with only a small corner. Dudu realized he had lost and sighed. He said, "OK, you win. Here is my joke: What do you call a fish that wears glasses? A see-fish!" Bubu laughed and hugged Dudu. She said, "That was a silly joke, but I love you anyway. Come here, I'll share the blanket with you." They cuddled together under the blanket and fell asleep happily. Moral: Sometimes, it’s OK to let your partner win, as long as you get a hug in return. _____ #bubududu #peachgoma #game #joke #couplefight #romantic #story #lover #goodnight #sleeptight #sweetdreams #bedtime #kidsstories #cutenessoverload #kawaii #cozy #winters #cuddle #blanketfight _______ -- © Varun Artist © #VarunArtist, @ #PeachGomaDiary u r not allowed to remove watermarks / edit parts / add ur texts, under any terms.
